225
00:07:11,962 --> 00:07:14,002
I have a rehearsal for the play right after the shoot.

226
00:07:14,402 --> 00:07:16,341
- Mister.
- Let's take a rain check.

227
00:07:16,342 --> 00:07:18,041
- He must be interested in her.
- I'm sorry.

228
00:07:18,042 --> 00:07:19,441
She has no choice...

229
00:07:19,442 --> 00:07:21,011
- as she has a rehearsal.
- She's scheduled for a rehearsal.

230
00:07:21,012 --> 00:07:23,181
You see, we stepped out for the shoot...

231
00:07:23,182 --> 00:07:24,381
- during a rehearsal.
- Oh, I see.

232
00:07:24,382 --> 00:07:26,111
- So we have to go back.
- You stepped out briefly.

233
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:28,881
- She can't miss the rehearsal.
- Are you from Incheon?

234
00:07:28,882 --> 00:07:30,921
- Yes, I am.
- Kyung Hwan, so are you.

235
00:07:30,922 --> 00:07:31,922
- The three of us are.
- You guys are from Incheon?

236
00:07:31,923 --> 00:07:33,221
- Yes, they're all from Incheon.
- Yes.

237
00:07:33,222 --> 00:07:34,421
- Kyu Han is from Incheon too.
- Well...

238
00:07:34,422 --> 00:07:36,661
My mother was born and raised in Incheon.

239
00:07:36,662 --> 00:07:37,791
The three of you are from Incheon. What about you, Two Swords?

240
00:07:37,792 --> 00:07:39,231
I'm not even from Incheon.

241
00:07:39,232 --> 00:07:41,391
- How is he even connected to them?
- We have nothing in common.

242
00:07:41,392 --> 00:07:44,861
I ate with Hee Jin in Incheon for a TV show.

243
00:07:44,862 --> 00:07:46,001
- That's right.
- What?

244
00:07:46,002 --> 00:07:47,271
- Going around a neighborhood.
- Yes.

245
00:07:47,272 --> 00:07:49,371
- She starred on "Dining Together?"
- I'm still amazed by something.

246
00:07:49,372 --> 00:07:53,141
She was 1 of the 3 prettiest girls in Incheon, which is a large city.

247
00:07:53,142 --> 00:07:55,111
- It's true. In Incheon...
- One of the three prettiest girls?

248
00:07:55,112 --> 00:07:56,211
- Oh, then...
- Kyung Hwan, tell us about it.

249
00:07:56,212 --> 00:07:57,311
- Of course, she was the prettiest.
- Stop it.

250
00:07:57,312 --> 00:07:58,781
- Then...
- I'll explain to you.

251
00:07:58,782 --> 00:08:00,951
There's a list of the pretty girls from Incheon...

252
00:08:00,952 --> 00:08:03,882
that's been handed down from generation to generation.

253
00:08:04,252 --> 00:08:06,791
- The first lady is Hwang Shin Hye.
- Hwang Shin Hye is from Incheon.

254
00:08:06,792 --> 00:08:08,451
- When I was little, I lived...
- She represents Incheon.

255
00:08:08,452 --> 00:08:10,622
- in the same neighborhood as her.
- She's beautiful.

256
00:08:10,822 --> 00:08:12,191
She had deep eyelid creases.

257
00:08:12,192 --> 00:08:14,131
- She looked like a pretty doll.
- Right. Her face is perfect.

258
00:08:14,132 --> 00:08:16,531
Shin Hye has a scientifically perfect face.

259
00:08:16,532 --> 00:08:17,931
- Yes, scientifically perfect.
- Next up is...

260
00:08:17,932 --> 00:08:20,632
- The second generation is...
- There are several ladies.

261
00:08:21,232 --> 00:08:24,141
I believe that the best winner of the Korean Super Model Contest is...

262
00:08:24,142 --> 00:08:26,241
- Lee So Ra.
- She's from Incheon.

263
00:08:26,242 --> 00:08:27,411
So Ra is from Incheon as well.

264
00:08:27,412 --> 00:08:30,781
The one who continued the tradition was Jun Ji Hyun of Incheon.

265
00:08:30,782 --> 00:08:31,981
(Hee Jin was called Jun Ji Hyun of Incheon.)

266
00:08:31,982 --> 00:08:33,211
Incheon Ji Hyun.

267
00:08:33,212 --> 00:08:35,511
- Jang Hee Jin.
- She was very famous...

268
00:08:35,512 --> 00:08:36,521
- as a gorgeous girl.
- Oh, I see.

269
00:08:36,522 --> 00:08:39,151
That's not true. I don't know where such a rumor started.

270
00:08:39,152 --> 00:08:40,992
- I heard you spread the rumor.
- That's right.

271
00:08:41,492 --> 00:08:43,791
I just said the rumor once, and it spread widely, I guess.

272
00:08:43,792 --> 00:08:45,721
- Hee Jin was really pretty.
- Before she debuted.

273
00:08:45,722 --> 00:08:47,761
I feel like Kyung Hwan came on the show several times.

274
00:08:47,762 --> 00:08:49,431
- But this is his first time here.
- Right.

275
00:08:49,432 --> 00:08:51,631
- I'm really worried...
- Why?

276
00:08:51,632 --> 00:08:53,631
because I came on a variety show after a very long time.

277
00:08:53,632 --> 00:08:56,271
I've been hosting a home shopping show for about 20 years now.

278
00:08:56,272 --> 00:08:57,741
Right. He's an expert in that field.

279
00:08:57,742 --> 00:09:01,771
I often work with lifeless objects on my home shopping show.

280
00:09:01,772 --> 00:09:03,412
- That's right.
- For example, a frying pan.

281
00:09:04,212 --> 00:09:05,512
It's a metal object.

282
00:09:06,082 --> 00:09:07,281
- That's right.
- Salted oysters.

283
00:09:07,282 --> 00:09:10,521
- What sells best?
- Kimchi, kkakdugi, galbitang,

284
00:09:10,522 --> 00:09:11,951
olive oil,

285
00:09:11,952 --> 00:09:13,391
- and organic lemon juice.
- They don't speak.

286
00:09:13,392 --> 00:09:14,621
Objects that don't speak.

287
00:09:14,622 --> 00:09:15,622
But here,

288
00:09:15,792 --> 00:09:17,591
so many people speak at the same time.

289
00:09:17,592 --> 00:09:20,231
You guys jump in while someone else is talking.

290
00:09:20,232 --> 00:09:21,962
I'm feeling a little bit dizzy now.

291
00:09:22,292 --> 00:09:23,501
- That makes sense.
- It's a little hard for me.

292
00:09:23,502 --> 00:09:27,172
Kyung Hwan, you said you hadn't been on a variety show in a while.

293
00:09:27,272 --> 00:09:30,001
- But from the viewers' perspective, - Exactly.

294
00:09:30,002 --> 00:09:32,101
- they see you very often.
- That's right.

295
00:09:32,102 --> 00:09:33,971
It feels like you're on many variety shows.

296
00:09:33,972 --> 00:09:35,572
- It's because...
- He hosts so many shows.

297
00:09:35,742 --> 00:09:37,041
Home shopping channels are...

298
00:09:37,042 --> 00:09:38,341
- between other types of channels.
- That's right.

299
00:09:38,342 --> 00:09:40,482
- They're between other channels.
- So when you switch channels,

300
00:09:40,782 --> 00:09:42,382
you can see Kyung Hwan on a home shopping channel.

301
00:09:42,752 --> 00:09:45,181
And then you see him again on another channel as well.

302
00:09:45,182 --> 00:09:46,651
That's right. Oh, you know that.

303
00:09:46,652 --> 00:09:49,052
We call it "zapping" in the home shopping field.

304
00:09:49,222 --> 00:09:51,592
For example, Men on a Mission ends.

305
00:09:51,722 --> 00:09:54,062
Then the viewers would switch channels at the same time.

306
00:09:54,332 --> 00:09:57,031
The moment when people switch to a home shopping channel,

307
00:09:57,032 --> 00:09:59,062
every show host would make an opening comment like this.

308
00:09:59,162 --> 00:10:02,102
- "We'll introduce our product."
- Really?

309
00:10:02,942 --> 00:10:04,202
When people switch channels.

310
00:10:04,302 --> 00:10:06,341
That's the best timing we can sell our products.

311
00:10:06,342 --> 00:10:07,812
- That's interesting.
- We must sell our products then.

312
00:10:07,872 --> 00:10:10,481
Jun Gyu has a lot of experience,

313
00:10:10,482 --> 00:10:12,442
so he can give the other guests advice.

314
00:10:12,542 --> 00:10:15,351
And apparently, he knows the characteristics...

315
00:10:15,352 --> 00:10:17,682
- of the cast members accurately.
- Really?

316
00:10:17,782 --> 00:10:19,991
- Please tell us.
- Tell us what you know about us.

317
00:10:19,992 --> 00:10:21,292
Hee Chul is cheery.

318
00:10:21,392 --> 00:10:22,422
As for Kyung Hoon,

319
00:10:23,422 --> 00:10:25,892
he's quiet when he doesn't like the female guests of the day.

320
00:10:26,762 --> 00:10:28,661
- That's accurate.
- He's been quiet all along.

321
00:10:28,662 --> 00:10:29,931
- He hasn't said a word until now.
- He has said no words.

322
00:10:29,932 --> 00:10:31,702
- Why...
- Why are you so quiet?

323
00:10:31,832 --> 00:10:33,171
It's not like that.

324
00:10:33,172 --> 00:10:35,032
- He's married now, so...
- He's married now.

325
00:10:35,472 --> 00:10:36,642
Are you being cautious?

326
00:10:37,502 --> 00:10:38,571
Are you being cautious?

327
00:10:38,572 --> 00:10:39,641
(Jang Hoon's gesture for asking for editing goes viral like a disease.)

328
00:10:39,642 --> 00:10:42,511
- He was like this before marriage.
- So many scenes will be edited.

329
00:10:42,512 --> 00:10:44,011
Today's episode...

330
00:10:44,012 --> 00:10:45,281
There's nothing we can air.

331
00:10:45,282 --> 00:10:47,852
Today's episode might be uploaded as short-form videos.

332
00:10:48,012 --> 00:10:49,111
Please go on. What about Jang Hoon?

333
00:10:49,112 --> 00:10:50,622
As you all know...

334
00:10:51,022 --> 00:10:52,221
when divorce is brought up,

335
00:10:52,222 --> 00:10:55,191
- he lets off steam.
- He lets off steam.

336
00:10:55,192 --> 00:10:56,661
And when Sang Min doesn't agree with him,

337
00:10:56,662 --> 00:10:58,592
- he gets really mad at Sang Min.
- That's right.

338
00:10:59,222 --> 00:11:00,962
(Jang Hoon, I'm okay.)

339
00:11:01,732 --> 00:11:04,202
(You should say it's not okay like I do!)

340
00:11:04,502 --> 00:11:06,901
(Vicarious anger)

341
00:11:06,902 --> 00:11:08,031
He'd tell Sang Min, "At least say a few words."

342
00:11:08,032 --> 00:11:11,742
As for Soo Geun, he always focuses only on his comments.

343
00:11:13,072 --> 00:11:15,271
- He wants to stand out.
- If it doesn't make him look funny,

344
00:11:15,272 --> 00:11:16,411
- he doesn't play along with a joke.
- He cares only about his comments.

345
00:11:16,412 --> 00:11:17,412
(If I make people laugh, that's all that matters.)

346
00:11:17,742 --> 00:11:21,012
He doesn't care. And Ho Dong always tries hard.

347
00:11:21,412 --> 00:11:22,552
He tries hard, and that's it?

348
00:11:23,222 --> 00:11:25,322
He doesn't have his own uniqueness. He just tries hard.

349
00:11:25,822 --> 00:11:27,121
- He tries hard.
- He has no uniqueness.

350
00:11:27,122 --> 00:11:29,592
(We applaud your hard work.)

351
00:11:30,122 --> 00:11:31,922
(Clapping with the feet)

352
00:11:32,292 --> 00:11:33,562
I will work harder to step my game up.

353
00:11:33,932 --> 00:11:35,061
- He works hard.
- Right.

354
00:11:35,062 --> 00:11:37,002
- What about Shin Dong?
- Hard work is important.

355
00:11:37,262 --> 00:11:39,731
Shin Dong is a great dancer,

356
00:11:39,732 --> 00:11:42,272
and I think he's a really good host.

357
00:11:42,402 --> 00:11:43,941
He stands out more in Part Two.

358
00:11:43,942 --> 00:11:45,272
(Shin Dong's character: Dancing king and a great MC)

359
00:11:45,902 --> 00:11:47,342
- He does know us well.
- Indeed.

360
00:11:48,172 --> 00:11:49,742
I have nothing to say about Yeong Cheol.

361
00:11:50,442 --> 00:11:51,981
I have nothing to say about Yeong Cheol.

362
00:11:51,982 --> 00:11:53,982
(The end)

363
00:11:54,052 --> 00:11:56,552
- It took so long to get to him.
- Yes, indeed.

364
00:11:57,382 --> 00:12:00,391
- You took all the time to say that?
- Yeong Cheol is cute.

365
00:12:00,392 --> 00:12:02,051
By the way, as far as I know,

366
00:12:02,052 --> 00:12:04,491
Yeong Cheol and Kyu Han are closely acquainted.

367
00:12:04,492 --> 00:12:06,662
We used to be very close to each other,

368
00:12:06,832 --> 00:12:08,192
but then we became distant from each other.

369
00:12:08,562 --> 00:12:09,802
- Oh, really?
- I wonder why.

370
00:12:09,932 --> 00:12:11,002
I guess he has no clue.

371
00:12:11,062 --> 00:12:13,771
- Did you two have a fight?
- We worked with the same agency.

372
00:12:13,772 --> 00:12:15,601
- That's right.
- I quit working with the agency...

373
00:12:15,602 --> 00:12:16,642
because of Yeong Cheol.

374
00:12:17,172 --> 00:12:18,771
- Was it that serious?
- Was it because of me?

375
00:12:18,772 --> 00:12:20,111
- Something happened between them.
- I'm getting goosebumps.

376
00:12:20,112 --> 00:12:23,181
Yeong Cheol and I became really close...

377
00:12:23,182 --> 00:12:24,711
- when we co-starred on "Real Men."
- That's right.

378
00:12:24,712 --> 00:12:26,351
We also worked with the same agency.

379
00:12:26,352 --> 00:12:28,481
When Yeong Cheol becomes acquainted with someone,

380
00:12:28,482 --> 00:12:31,122
he talks the person into going on the shows he's on.

381
00:12:31,322 --> 00:12:33,791
- So I appeared on his radio show...
- I didn't help him get cast.

382
00:12:33,792 --> 00:12:35,951
and went on this show related fashion...

383
00:12:35,952 --> 00:12:37,622
that he just started hosting.

384
00:12:37,822 --> 00:12:40,892
After that, I got a role in a new drama.

385
00:12:41,162 --> 00:12:44,061
I was asked if there was anyone I could ask...

386
00:12:44,062 --> 00:12:45,631
to play a cameo role in the drama.

387
00:12:45,632 --> 00:12:47,802
I said there was this person who would definitely do it...

388
00:12:48,432 --> 00:12:50,641
and that there was no way Yeong Cheol would turn me down.

389
00:12:50,642 --> 00:12:51,801
- Right.
- So...

390
00:12:51,802 --> 00:12:55,242
- The script for him came out.
- Stars help each other like that.

391
00:12:55,772 --> 00:12:57,611
He was going to play a man who wouldn't stop talking.

392
00:12:57,612 --> 00:12:59,552
A new character was created, and the script came out.

393
00:12:59,852 --> 00:13:01,182
But he refused to play the role.

394
00:13:01,652 --> 00:13:03,022
- What?
- Why?

395
00:13:03,952 --> 00:13:05,581
- It wasn't a novel character.
- What's the reason?

396
00:13:05,582 --> 00:13:08,322
- Why did he refuse?
- He's the type that's willing...

397
00:13:08,422 --> 00:13:10,021
- to ask for a role. So why?
- Exactly.

398
00:13:10,022 --> 00:13:11,391
I was asked why he refused.

399
00:13:11,392 --> 00:13:14,461
But I thought it'd hurt my pride to ask him why.

400
00:13:14,462 --> 00:13:17,232
So I asked my agency why he refused the role.

401
00:13:17,402 --> 00:13:20,271
Apparently, he decided not to play any cameo roles...

402
00:13:20,272 --> 00:13:21,902
unless he appeared in most episodes of a series.

403
00:13:22,602 --> 00:13:24,041
- Why?
- He thought cameo wasn't his thing.

404
00:13:24,042 --> 00:13:25,141
- So I understood.
- Yes.

405
00:13:25,142 --> 00:13:27,242
But after a while, I found out...

406
00:13:27,742 --> 00:13:30,211
that he play a cameo role in a drama that Kim Hee Seon starred in.

407
00:13:30,212 --> 00:13:31,582
- My gosh.
- Really?

408
00:13:32,542 --> 00:13:33,911
- This...
- He had a reason to be upset.

409
00:13:33,912 --> 00:13:35,082
I can't defend him on this.

410
00:13:35,612 --> 00:13:37,252
- Look. Ho Dong doesn't talk to him.
- After that,

411
00:13:37,322 --> 00:13:39,722
I deleted Yeong Cheol's number from my phone.

412
00:13:40,452 --> 00:13:41,521
That's understandable.

413
00:13:41,522 --> 00:13:42,692
You haven't met him ever since?

414
00:13:43,122 --> 00:13:44,491
- Yeong Cheol.
- That's understandable.

415
00:13:44,492 --> 00:13:45,921
Yeong Cheol, ask them to edit this out.

416
00:13:45,922 --> 00:13:47,632
- What did you say I should do?
- Ask them to edit it out.

417
00:13:48,162 --> 00:13:49,802
I think I'll be okay even if it airs.

418
00:13:51,332 --> 00:13:52,532
- What?
- He's confident.

419
00:13:53,072 --> 00:13:55,631
- Or I won't get much air time.
- It's a funny story, right?

420
00:13:55,632 --> 00:13:56,671
It's a story about him after all.

421
00:13:56,672 --> 00:13:58,001
They can put an on-screen text...

422
00:13:58,002 --> 00:13:59,341
- saying we're good friends now.
- It's a story about him...

423
00:13:59,342 --> 00:14:00,611
- after all.
- He's the protagonist in it.

424
00:14:00,612 --> 00:14:03,012
- As long as it's about him.
- We can make peace now.

425
00:14:03,112 --> 00:14:04,341
- You're making peace suddenly?
- Of course.

426
00:14:04,342 --> 00:14:05,581
- Kyu Han doesn't seem to be ready.
- Exactly.

427
00:14:05,582 --> 00:14:07,011
- He seems scared.
- Kyu Han, I'm so sorry.

428
00:14:07,012 --> 00:14:08,211
They'll probably edit this part out.

429
00:14:08,212 --> 00:14:09,551
Kyu Han, I'm very sorry.

430
00:14:09,552 --> 00:14:10,651
This will probably be edited out.

431
00:14:10,652 --> 00:14:11,752
- Okay.
- My gosh.

432
00:14:12,182 --> 00:14:13,352
- What?
- What's going on?

433
00:14:13,922 --> 00:14:14,991
Sit down.

434
00:14:14,992 --> 00:14:16,791
Why would you make it a big deal when it's nothing?

435
00:14:16,792 --> 00:14:18,062
- What? What's going on?
- Do you have something to say?

436
00:14:18,722 --> 00:14:19,761
- What? What's going on?
- Do you have something to say?

437
00:14:19,762 --> 00:14:20,832
Give me your transfer form.

438
00:14:21,232 --> 00:14:22,761
- Oh, I see.
- He came for the transfer form?

439
00:14:22,762 --> 00:14:23,831
- I don't have my phone with me.
- Give it to me.

440
00:14:23,832 --> 00:14:25,801
I didn't ask for your phone. I asked for your transfer form.

441
00:14:25,802 --> 00:14:27,401
- Your phone?
- He said he didn't have his phone.

442
00:14:27,402 --> 00:14:29,102
- I thought Sang Min was...
- Why would I...

443
00:14:29,202 --> 00:14:30,401
- taking his phone away from him.
- I asked for the transfer form.

444
00:14:30,402 --> 00:14:32,802
- I thought he asked for my phone.
- Exactly.

445
00:14:33,142 --> 00:14:35,112
- Sang Min became quite aggressive.
- I thought...

446
00:14:35,212 --> 00:14:37,082
- he came here to hit Kyu Han.
- He must be stressed out a lot.

447
00:14:37,612 --> 00:14:39,751
Why are you being like this when you just got married?

448
00:14:39,752 --> 00:14:41,081
- Why did he do that suddenly?
- What was that?

449
00:14:41,082 --> 00:14:42,481
- What is going on?
- Say something to your niblings.

450
00:14:42,482 --> 00:14:43,982
Kids, your uncle is working hard.

451
00:14:45,622 --> 00:14:46,751
That's great.

452
00:14:46,752 --> 00:14:49,051
- Your uncle is awesome.
- Of course.

453
00:14:49,052 --> 00:14:50,962
- This is nice too.
- You can sit down now.

454
00:14:51,492 --> 00:14:53,561
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

455
00:14:53,562 --> 00:14:55,091
Names, Park Jun Gyu, Yeom Kyung Hwan,

456
00:14:55,092 --> 00:14:56,632
Lee Kyu Han, and Jang Hee Jin.

457
00:14:57,062 --> 00:14:58,401
(Welcome)

458
00:14:58,402 --> 00:15:01,901
First up is the school transfer standard.

459
00:15:01,902 --> 00:15:04,442
Their answer is "Mister."

460
00:15:05,102 --> 00:15:06,441
Let's be honest to one another.

461
00:15:06,442 --> 00:15:08,971
Raise your hand if you think you're an old man.

462
00:15:08,972 --> 00:15:10,112
Do you consider yourselves an old man?

463
00:15:10,242 --> 00:15:11,441
One, two, three.

464
00:15:11,442 --> 00:15:12,742
- An old man...
- Of course, I'm an old man.

465
00:15:13,012 --> 00:15:15,612
- I never thought I was an old man.
- Me neither.

466
00:15:15,812 --> 00:15:18,222
(Soo Geun, Sang Min, Jang Hoon, and Jun Gyu don't think they are.)

467
00:15:18,322 --> 00:15:22,851
- Here's why I didn't raise my hand.
- I raised my hand.

468
00:15:22,852 --> 00:15:25,391
Anyone who knows who I am including children would say,

469
00:15:25,392 --> 00:15:28,091
"Hey, that's Seo Jang Hoon."

470
00:15:28,092 --> 00:15:30,531
- Not "Mr. Seo." I get it.
- That's right.

471
00:15:30,532 --> 00:15:32,932
Even a seven-year-old kid would say, "Oh, he's Seo Jang Hoon."

472
00:15:33,032 --> 00:15:34,631
- They don't call me "Mr. Seo."
- That's true.

473
00:15:34,632 --> 00:15:36,741
So I rarely see people addressing me as an old man.

474
00:15:36,742 --> 00:15:38,472
People usually address celebrities without any title.

475
00:15:38,642 --> 00:15:40,242
Jun Gyu, why don't you think you're an old man?

476
00:15:40,372 --> 00:15:41,512
I'm a grandpa, not just an old man.

477
00:15:42,142 --> 00:15:44,041
(He won't even claim to be just an old man.)

478
00:15:44,042 --> 00:15:45,441
- I mean...
- He's a grandpa.

479
00:15:45,442 --> 00:15:48,711
Let me explain. When I take an elevator...

480
00:15:48,712 --> 00:15:52,181
- with some kids and their parents, - Right.

481
00:15:52,182 --> 00:15:54,592
the parents always tell their kids...

482
00:15:55,052 --> 00:15:56,561
to greet me...

483
00:15:56,562 --> 00:15:58,621
addressing me as "a grandpa," not as "an middle-aged man."

484
00:15:58,622 --> 00:15:59,622
That makes sense.

485
00:15:59,623 --> 00:16:02,191
- I don't understand.
- It's relative, you know.

486
00:16:02,192 --> 00:16:03,461
From teens' perspective,

487
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:05,461
- men in their 20s and 30s are old.
- That's right.

488
00:16:05,462 --> 00:16:08,472
What age do you think a man should be considered "old?"

489
00:16:09,002 --> 00:16:10,641
Men aged 40 and over, I think.

490
00:16:10,642 --> 00:16:12,802
- I think men aged 30 and over.
- I don't think age matters.

491
00:16:13,142 --> 00:16:15,711
- You see, this is...
- Whether or not you can talk...

492
00:16:15,712 --> 00:16:17,041
to young people...

493
00:16:17,042 --> 00:16:18,942
determines if you're old, in my opinion.

494
00:16:19,112 --> 00:16:20,951
- He has a point.
- If you can't talk to them...

495
00:16:20,952 --> 00:16:22,581
or can't understand what they say, you're old.

496
00:16:22,582 --> 00:16:24,982
We should be clear about this topic.

497
00:16:25,122 --> 00:16:27,392
If someone tells his juniors or little kids...

498
00:16:27,592 --> 00:16:29,291
to address him like a big brother,

499
00:16:29,292 --> 00:16:31,721
- he's an old man.
- Right. That's the worst.

500
00:16:31,722 --> 00:16:33,161
- Telling them such a thing...
- Telling them what to call you...

501
00:16:33,162 --> 00:16:34,162
- That's the worst.
- That's right.

502
00:16:34,163 --> 00:16:35,191
You really shouldn't do that.

503
00:16:35,192 --> 00:16:36,461
Back in the day, people considered...

504
00:16:36,462 --> 00:16:37,732
- a man in a sleeveless shirt old.
- A sleeveless shirt.

505
00:16:38,132 --> 00:16:40,131
- That's right.
- One with a saggy neckline.

506
00:16:40,132 --> 00:16:41,602
- A white one.
- Back in the day,

507
00:16:41,772 --> 00:16:44,402
old men would wear a sleeveless undershirt outside.

508
00:16:45,102 --> 00:16:47,442
Your nipples are quite visible when you wear it.

509
00:16:47,912 --> 00:16:49,781
- Forget what people call you.
- This part would be revealed too.

510
00:16:49,782 --> 00:16:53,312
When do you feel like you're an old man?

511
00:16:53,452 --> 00:16:56,682
To be honest, I used to be aloof.

512
00:16:56,952 --> 00:16:59,722
When I was asked a question, I gave short answers.

513
00:17:00,422 --> 00:17:02,552
Or I refused to answer the question.

514
00:17:02,952 --> 00:17:05,621
But recently, I started to give lengthy answers.

515
00:17:05,622 --> 00:17:07,161
- That's right.
- You become chatty.

516
00:17:07,162 --> 00:17:09,061
- You talk long and idly.
- You need to explain the details.

517
00:17:09,062 --> 00:17:11,462
- You become talkative.
- I would start with "Listen."

518
00:17:12,062 --> 00:17:13,771
(The intro already makes it boring.)

519
00:17:13,772 --> 00:17:14,931
- Right.
- That's right.

520
00:17:14,932 --> 00:17:16,072
- "Think carefully."
- Right.

521
00:17:16,402 --> 00:17:17,402
- That's an old fossil.
- Right.

522
00:17:17,403 --> 00:17:19,741
When I was younger, when my junior actor asked me...

523
00:17:19,742 --> 00:17:22,012
for advice on acting during a shoot,

524
00:17:22,312 --> 00:17:24,311
I gave a brief, concise answer.

525
00:17:24,312 --> 00:17:27,482
But now I give a long speech. "Listen. You stand here..."

526
00:17:27,712 --> 00:17:29,551
As I go on, I see the dark circles under his eyes...

527
00:17:29,552 --> 00:17:31,381
- getting deeper and deeper.
- Of course.

528
00:17:31,382 --> 00:17:33,792
And he seems like he regrets asking for my advice.

529
00:17:33,992 --> 00:17:35,321
That's when I realized I'm old now.

530
00:17:35,322 --> 00:17:37,862
I realize I'm old now...

531
00:17:38,162 --> 00:17:40,392
when I see myself singing while doing something.

532
00:17:40,862 --> 00:17:42,431
I put a melody to the words I want to say without noticing.

533
00:17:42,432 --> 00:17:44,931
- What should I eat today?
- Even when I'm alone. That's it.

534
00:17:44,932 --> 00:17:46,061
You do that when you open your fridge too.

535
00:17:46,062 --> 00:17:47,272
Let's say...

536
00:17:47,472 --> 00:17:49,602
- I'm alone and cooking ramyeon.
- Yes.

537
00:17:50,072 --> 00:17:53,411
All right, where is ramyeon? Let me see

538
00:17:53,412 --> 00:17:54,541
- You add notes to the words.
- So it wasn't just me.

539
00:17:54,542 --> 00:17:56,271
- You add notes to the words.
- Oh, no, that's not it

540
00:17:56,272 --> 00:17:58,781
- Kimchi - Where is kimchi?

541
00:17:58,782 --> 00:18:01,011
Oh, no, this one is too fermented

542
00:18:01,012 --> 00:18:02,652
I sing like this without even realizing I'm doing it.

543
00:18:02,812 --> 00:18:04,822
- When there's no one around you?
- That's right.

544
00:18:05,622 --> 00:18:08,422
- I sing without realizing it.
- Right.

545
00:18:08,522 --> 00:18:10,622
When I put my clothes back on after a sauna,

546
00:18:10,862 --> 00:18:13,862
I sit down to wear socks.

547
00:18:14,032 --> 00:18:16,902
- Right. You need to sit down.
- I used to do it while standing.

548
00:18:17,032 --> 00:18:19,362
(While everyone else can relate to him...)

549
00:18:20,032 --> 00:18:21,871
- I need to lean on something...
- What?

550
00:18:21,872 --> 00:18:23,701
- to stand up.
- Do some wear socks while standing?

551
00:18:23,702 --> 00:18:25,072
- Wear socks while standing?
- You...

552
00:18:26,742 --> 00:18:29,172
Shin Dong couldn't relate to it.

553
00:18:29,572 --> 00:18:31,282
- Do you wear socks while standing?
- What?

554
00:18:31,682 --> 00:18:33,281
- Do you wear socks while standing?
- The two of them must be the same.

555
00:18:33,282 --> 00:18:35,281
- I can do it while standing, - Of course.

556
00:18:35,282 --> 00:18:36,822
- but I need to lean on the wall.
- That's right.

557
00:18:36,922 --> 00:18:38,181
- You mean, you wear them like this.
- Shin Dong.

558
00:18:38,182 --> 00:18:39,851
- I need something to lean on.
- Really?

559
00:18:39,852 --> 00:18:42,051
- So you don't do it while standing.
- Or else, I can't do it.

560
00:18:42,052 --> 00:18:44,021
What makes you feel like you're old?

561
00:18:44,022 --> 00:18:46,421
I feel that sometimes. When I enter a room,

562
00:18:46,422 --> 00:18:48,562
the people who arrived before me...

563
00:18:48,732 --> 00:18:50,102
stand up as I walk in.

564
00:18:50,432 --> 00:18:52,932
(That proves that he became the oldest among old men.)

565
00:18:53,632 --> 00:18:56,201
- "Why are you standing up?"
- Right.

566
00:18:56,202 --> 00:18:57,471
- I ask them not to do so.
- Right.

567
00:18:57,472 --> 00:18:59,171
But based on the documentary I watched,

568
00:18:59,172 --> 00:19:01,142
people always stood up when they saw you even before.

569
00:19:02,072 --> 00:19:04,111
Ever since he was young, like back in school.

570
00:19:04,112 --> 00:19:05,481
Anyone would get up, without a doubt.

571
00:19:05,482 --> 00:19:07,611
Anywhere he goes, I'm sure everyone will get up.

572
00:19:07,612 --> 00:19:09,582
Everyone will get up without thinking.

573
00:19:09,882 --> 00:19:11,522
- Out of habit.
- Exactly.

574
00:19:11,852 --> 00:19:14,192
Come to think of it, I'm still curious.

575
00:19:14,292 --> 00:19:17,322
Don't you feel out of place here with these old men?

576
00:19:17,522 --> 00:19:18,921
In fact, she's today's biggest victim.

577
00:19:18,922 --> 00:19:19,962
Right?

578
00:19:20,062 --> 00:19:22,431
Are there times when you feel like...

579
00:19:22,432 --> 00:19:24,231
- you've aged?
- Yes, and a lot at that.

580
00:19:24,232 --> 00:19:26,672
Have you ever been called "Aunt?"

581
00:19:26,872 --> 00:19:29,832
- I did, but only recently.
- I see.

582
00:19:30,072 --> 00:19:32,701
My car was hot, so I rolled down the windows.

583
00:19:32,702 --> 00:19:34,472
I was about to pull my car out...

584
00:19:34,612 --> 00:19:36,781
when a child around 3 to 4 years old...

585
00:19:36,782 --> 00:19:38,342
- They only say the truth.
- Right.

586
00:19:38,582 --> 00:19:40,551
They said, "An old woman!"

587
00:19:40,552 --> 00:19:42,212
- Out of the blue?
- Suddenly?

588
00:19:42,312 --> 00:19:43,951
- Without a reason?
- Pointing at me...

589
00:19:43,952 --> 00:19:45,221
- through the open window, - Just...

590
00:19:45,222 --> 00:19:47,052
they said, "You're an old woman, right?"

591
00:19:47,122 --> 00:19:49,821
Hee Jin said she could feel herself aging,

592
00:19:49,822 --> 00:19:51,722
but those around her noticed it more.

593
00:19:51,992 --> 00:19:53,761
- The fact that she's old.
- How come?

594
00:19:53,762 --> 00:19:55,261
- What are you saying?
- First off...

595
00:19:55,262 --> 00:19:57,261
Getting angry proves that you're an old man.

596
00:19:57,262 --> 00:19:59,131
- The temper...
- Old women carry a lot of anger.

597
00:19:59,132 --> 00:20:00,402
- It's the same with us.
- Like this.

598
00:20:00,432 --> 00:20:02,231
Call us "old man," and we're like, "What?"

599
00:20:02,232 --> 00:20:03,972
You got upset over such a trivial comment.

600
00:20:04,742 --> 00:20:08,172
Because we're in a play together, we have a group chat.

601
00:20:08,372 --> 00:20:10,281
After work, we sent each other...

602
00:20:10,282 --> 00:20:12,311
messages saying, "Great job today."

603
00:20:12,312 --> 00:20:14,952
But she keeps mentioning people who aren't in the chat.

604
00:20:14,982 --> 00:20:16,251
- In the chat?
- Who don't exist.

605
00:20:16,252 --> 00:20:18,621
People who don't exist. For example, someone who's not here.

606
00:20:18,622 --> 00:20:21,122
- She sends, "Great work, Hye Jin."
- Right.

607
00:20:21,152 --> 00:20:22,721
- Who's Hye Jin?
- I'm like, "Who's Hye Jin?"

608
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:24,122
There's no Hye Jin.

609
00:20:24,322 --> 00:20:25,691
No one with that name exists.

610
00:20:25,692 --> 00:20:28,892
Last time, she sent, "Yoon, where was that parking lot again?"

611
00:20:28,962 --> 00:20:30,432
No Yoon exists in our chat room.

612
00:20:31,002 --> 00:20:33,902
Her name was Seon Woo. Yoon Seon Woo.

613
00:20:34,002 --> 00:20:36,601
But I only memorized Yoon and not Seon Woo.

614
00:20:36,602 --> 00:20:38,302
- So you called her "Yoon?"
- "Yoon?"

615
00:20:38,402 --> 00:20:41,512
There are about 15 people in our chat.

616
00:20:41,912 --> 00:20:43,982
Half are in their 40s,

617
00:20:44,142 --> 00:20:47,382
and the rest are in their 20s. In their 20s to early 30s.

618
00:20:47,452 --> 00:20:50,381
People in their 40s talk 90 percent of the time.

619
00:20:50,382 --> 00:20:51,821
- True.
- Yes.

620
00:20:51,822 --> 00:20:53,081
- Right.
- Old men talk a lot.

621
00:20:53,082 --> 00:20:55,621
I bet there's a separate youngsters' chat.

622
00:20:55,622 --> 00:20:57,061
- That's what I think.
- I'm sure they do.

623
00:20:57,062 --> 00:20:58,092
"Youngsters' chat?"

624
00:20:58,262 --> 00:21:00,661
Yes, unless they have a separate youngsters' chat...

625
00:21:00,662 --> 00:21:02,791
- "Youngsters' chat."
- That term itself was...

626
00:21:02,792 --> 00:21:05,461
- It upsets me.
- "Youngsters."

627
00:21:05,462 --> 00:21:06,701
- "Youngsters."
- "Youngsters."

628
00:21:06,702 --> 00:21:08,172
- They definitely have one.
- It's upsetting.

629
00:21:08,232 --> 00:21:10,572
- About sending messages.
- Yes?

630
00:21:10,772 --> 00:21:12,302
- The musical I'm currently in...
- Yes?

631
00:21:12,502 --> 00:21:14,772
- has a group chat with 66 people.
- I see.

632
00:21:14,872 --> 00:21:16,472
I have not sent a single message.

633
00:21:16,612 --> 00:21:18,641
- How come?
- People might call me an old man.

634
00:21:18,642 --> 00:21:21,852
What? He's the definition of an old man.

635
00:21:22,012 --> 00:21:23,482
- You're a real old man.
- I...

636
00:21:23,952 --> 00:21:25,681
Not being able to join makes you an old man.

637
00:21:25,682 --> 00:21:29,092
I really felt the need to be careful.

638
00:21:29,192 --> 00:21:30,692
- Life is so boring.
- I know.

639
00:21:31,292 --> 00:21:32,791
- It's boring?
- I don't know.

640
00:21:32,792 --> 00:21:34,462
Saying your life is boring came out of the blue.

641
00:21:35,032 --> 00:21:38,032
Not being able to live the way I want makes life boring.

642
00:21:38,502 --> 00:21:40,931
That's something you need to take care of.

643
00:21:40,932 --> 00:21:42,201
(A tough old man)

644
00:21:42,202 --> 00:21:44,271
- Do take care of it yourself.
- Yes.

645
00:21:44,272 --> 00:21:46,272
- It's a personal matter.
- Jun Gyu is sad.

646
00:21:46,942 --> 00:21:49,572
Moving on, the next one is "friendship."

647
00:21:49,942 --> 00:21:52,411
Jun Gyu and Kyung Hwan...

648
00:21:52,412 --> 00:21:55,011
wrote, "Only two sons."

649
00:21:55,012 --> 00:21:56,151
He's right.

650
00:21:56,152 --> 00:21:59,451
Now that your children are older, don't they know each other?

651
00:21:59,452 --> 00:22:01,421
- During "Junior Show,"
- "Junior Show."

652
00:22:01,422 --> 00:22:03,121
- We were all on the show.
- they saw each other every week.

653
00:22:03,122 --> 00:22:05,021
- They were really famous back then.
- I remember.

654
00:22:05,022 --> 00:22:07,531
When we went to restaurants, people told my son that...

655
00:22:07,532 --> 00:22:09,091
- they were enjoying "Junior Show."
- Same here.

656
00:22:09,092 --> 00:22:10,932
That was more common back then.

657
00:22:11,002 --> 00:22:13,002
- I...
- Three years old?

658
00:22:13,202 --> 00:22:15,771
I just found out that his eldest son is over 30.

659
00:22:15,772 --> 00:22:18,071
- What?
- Really? Already?

660
00:22:18,072 --> 00:22:19,971
Some of you attended his wedding.

661
00:22:19,972 --> 00:22:21,312
- Yes, he's married.
- He's 34 years old.

662
00:22:22,012 --> 00:22:24,142
The boy who appeared on "Junior Show" is now 28.

663
00:22:24,342 --> 00:22:26,341
Jun Gyu's family...

664
00:22:26,342 --> 00:22:28,611
has been in acting...

665
00:22:28,612 --> 00:22:30,282
- for three generations.
- Really?

666
00:22:30,422 --> 00:22:32,182
They are giving it their all.

667
00:22:32,352 --> 00:22:33,921
They've also gone through a lot.

668
00:22:33,922 --> 00:22:35,722
I told them to keep working hard...

669
00:22:35,892 --> 00:22:37,821
and building their careers,

670
00:22:37,822 --> 00:22:40,532
and that once they find the perfect role...

671
00:22:40,592 --> 00:22:43,501
and it becomes successful, they would settle.

672
00:22:43,502 --> 00:22:45,732
They're still working so hard, and it really breaks my heart.

673
00:22:45,932 --> 00:22:47,532
- Why?
- When I watch them.

674
00:22:47,632 --> 00:22:49,401
- Do you feel bad for them?
- "Your grandfather..."

675
00:22:49,402 --> 00:22:51,301
"was a famous man. So is your father."

676
00:22:51,302 --> 00:22:54,272
I told my sons that people would keep saying that to them.

677
00:22:54,372 --> 00:22:56,341
People used to keep calling me...

678
00:22:56,342 --> 00:22:58,012
"Park No Shik's son,"

679
00:22:58,082 --> 00:22:59,412
which really stressed me out.

680
00:22:59,742 --> 00:23:02,511
My sons are following the same path.

681
00:23:02,512 --> 00:23:03,781
- Two Swords' son.
- Yes.

682
00:23:03,782 --> 00:23:05,781
People have already called them that a lot.

683
00:23:05,782 --> 00:23:07,392
"Push through it."

684
00:23:07,752 --> 00:23:09,251
That was the advice I gave them.

685
00:23:09,252 --> 00:23:12,561
I met Jun Gyu for the first time today.

686
00:23:12,562 --> 00:23:15,261
But about ten years ago...

687
00:23:15,262 --> 00:23:17,162
in Apgujeong-dong,

688
00:23:17,202 --> 00:23:20,272
it was quite an eventful day, either Christmas...

689
00:23:20,372 --> 00:23:22,932
or Valentine's Day. I don't remember.

690
00:23:23,032 --> 00:23:24,871
I saw him leaving...

691
00:23:24,872 --> 00:23:27,412
a very famous chocolate store, wearing a caramel-colored coat...

692
00:23:27,512 --> 00:23:31,542
and carrying a gift-wrapped box of chocolates.

693
00:23:31,912 --> 00:23:36,352
After that, I watched a documentary of Jun Gyu's family.

694
00:23:36,782 --> 00:23:39,381
I thought, "It would be so cool..."

695
00:23:39,382 --> 00:23:42,152
"to be a husband and dad like that."

696
00:23:42,392 --> 00:23:43,591
He's a very cool man.

697
00:23:43,592 --> 00:23:45,292
You gave that chocolate to your wife, right?

698
00:23:46,022 --> 00:23:47,431
- That chocolate.
- Tell us.

699
00:23:47,432 --> 00:23:48,591
Did you take it home?

700
00:23:48,592 --> 00:23:49,961
- You gave it to your family, right?
- Jun Gyu.

701
00:23:49,962 --> 00:23:52,102
Wait a minute. Kyu Han.

702
00:23:52,262 --> 00:23:53,872
- Why did you have to...
- I'm sorry.

703
00:23:54,002 --> 00:23:56,601
I didn't bring it up to cause any trouble.

704
00:23:56,602 --> 00:23:59,141
You took that chocolate home, right?

705
00:23:59,142 --> 00:24:02,541
If his wife didn't eat that chocolate...

706
00:24:02,542 --> 00:24:03,711
It's a problem.

707
00:24:03,712 --> 00:24:06,342
If she didn't, it would be a huge problem.

708
00:24:06,682 --> 00:24:09,382
I got it for myself to eat whenever I needed a pick-me-up.

709
00:24:09,552 --> 00:24:11,122
So it was for yourself.

710
00:24:11,222 --> 00:24:13,081
But the wrapping was way too fancy.

711
00:24:13,082 --> 00:24:15,621
Stop it! Enough!

712
00:24:15,622 --> 00:24:17,362
- Stop!
- It was a gift for himself.

713
00:24:18,322 --> 00:24:19,421
He looks flustered.

714
00:24:19,422 --> 00:24:21,462
No, it's just a hilarious story.

715
00:24:22,292 --> 00:24:24,632
Right. It'd be hilarious since you didn't take it home.

716
00:24:24,732 --> 00:24:28,001
My friends and family...

717
00:24:28,002 --> 00:24:30,672
- are most jealous of this TV show.
- I see.

718
00:24:30,872 --> 00:24:32,202
Whenever I say I'm coming on this show,

719
00:24:32,402 --> 00:24:34,811
they know I'll have a great time with you all.

720
00:24:34,812 --> 00:24:37,942
Aren't you trying too hard to make this a comedy show?

721
00:24:38,142 --> 00:24:39,541
Ever since the chocolate story,

722
00:24:39,542 --> 00:24:42,051
- he's been stuttering nonstop.
- His...

723
00:24:42,052 --> 00:24:43,151
reactions are...

724
00:24:43,152 --> 00:24:45,121
The chocolate story wasn't for fun.

725
00:24:45,122 --> 00:24:46,951
We were being serious, you know?

726
00:24:46,952 --> 00:24:48,221
Think about it.

727
00:24:48,222 --> 00:24:50,621
How could I possibly remember buying...

728
00:24:50,622 --> 00:24:53,492
chocolates in Apgujeong-dong a decade ago?

729
00:24:53,962 --> 00:24:54,991
No.

730
00:24:54,992 --> 00:24:57,101
But your wife might remember it.

731
00:24:57,102 --> 00:24:59,131
Whether she received the chocolate or not.

732
00:24:59,132 --> 00:25:01,072
- It would've been a meaningful day.
- Yes.

733
00:25:01,972 --> 00:25:03,772
Fine.

734
00:25:03,872 --> 00:25:06,471
(Case closed)

735
00:25:06,472 --> 00:25:08,172
- Goodness.
- "Fine."

736
00:25:08,612 --> 00:25:12,042
Come on. We're meeting after a long time.

737
00:25:14,612 --> 00:25:15,981
He hit the nail on the head.

738
00:25:15,982 --> 00:25:17,851
- Jun Gyu is hilarious.
- For real.

739
00:25:17,852 --> 00:25:19,922
Why bring up chocolate all of a sudden?

740
00:25:20,622 --> 00:25:21,721
(Feeling wronged)

741
00:25:21,722 --> 00:25:22,751
My side hurts.

742
00:25:22,752 --> 00:25:25,492
If you were buying in secret, you should've hidden your face.

743
00:25:25,962 --> 00:25:29,031
Kyung Hwan, you haven't worked as a comedian for a long time.

744
00:25:29,032 --> 00:25:30,602
- No, I haven't.
- Your children...

745
00:25:30,902 --> 00:25:33,031
must not know about your past.

746
00:25:33,032 --> 00:25:34,172
My eldest does.

747
00:25:34,502 --> 00:25:36,872
Since he was on "Junior Show" with you.

748
00:25:37,172 --> 00:25:39,441
- My eldest son...
- How old is Eun Yul right now?

749
00:25:39,442 --> 00:25:40,672
He's old enough to join the military.

750
00:25:40,842 --> 00:25:42,541
- He needs to serve in the military.
- What?

751
00:25:42,542 --> 00:25:44,381
- The military.
- Did he already join?

752
00:25:44,382 --> 00:25:45,911
- Recently?
- He went to the military?

753
00:25:45,912 --> 00:25:47,311
- He applied for KATUSA.
- He was a baby.

754
00:25:47,312 --> 00:25:48,982
- He's already that old?
- Yes.

755
00:25:49,152 --> 00:25:51,081
My second son is now in fifth grade.

756
00:25:51,082 --> 00:25:52,221
He's quite young.

757
00:25:52,222 --> 00:25:53,451
You must get along well with your wife.

758
00:25:53,452 --> 00:25:55,821
That explains why he doesn't know you're a comedian.

759
00:25:55,822 --> 00:25:57,161
- My second son?
- Yes.

760
00:25:57,162 --> 00:25:58,891
If he watches TV...

761
00:25:58,892 --> 00:26:00,831
when Men on a Mission airs,

762
00:26:00,832 --> 00:26:02,231
- "Wait."
- "Why is Dad on the show?"

763
00:26:02,232 --> 00:26:03,462
he'll be like, "What? Why is Dad on the show?"

764
00:26:03,862 --> 00:26:05,832
"Is this a new home shopping show?"

765
00:26:06,032 --> 00:26:07,531
"What is Dad trying to sell?"

766
00:26:07,532 --> 00:26:08,731
(Second son is about to be surprised!)

767
00:26:08,732 --> 00:26:11,202
- "Why is Dad on the show?"
- To sell chocolates.

768
00:26:11,372 --> 00:26:12,541
My second son has no idea.

769
00:26:12,542 --> 00:26:14,841
My son was way more popular than I was...

770
00:26:14,842 --> 00:26:17,511
- when he was on "Junior Show."
- Right.

771
00:26:17,512 --> 00:26:20,351
- He had that really curly perm.
- Yes.

772
00:26:20,352 --> 00:26:22,081
- I remember.
- I thought...

773
00:26:22,082 --> 00:26:25,852
maybe he'd become a celebrity with all that talent.

774
00:26:26,022 --> 00:26:28,891
But he has zero interest in the entertainment industry.

775
00:26:28,892 --> 00:26:30,891
He's currently into webcomics.

776
00:26:30,892 --> 00:26:32,061
- Gosh.
- Really?

777
00:26:32,062 --> 00:26:35,531
He's drawing webcomics right now.

778
00:26:35,532 --> 00:26:37,402
Does your second son want to become a comedian?

779
00:26:37,602 --> 00:26:39,662
- He's an odd one.
- Why?

780
00:26:40,472 --> 00:26:43,231
I called my son because he wasn't coming home.

781
00:26:43,232 --> 00:26:45,272
Children these days all carry a phone.

782
00:26:45,642 --> 00:26:47,041
I asked where he was.

783
00:26:47,042 --> 00:26:48,342
It was past 9pm.

784
00:26:48,872 --> 00:26:50,681
He was at a gukbap place.

785
00:26:50,682 --> 00:26:52,081
- With whom?
- A grade schooler?

786
00:26:52,082 --> 00:26:53,582
- Gukbap.
- But he's a grade schooler.

787
00:26:53,682 --> 00:26:54,982
Yes, a grade schooler.

788
00:26:55,082 --> 00:26:56,512
"Who are you with?"

789
00:26:57,022 --> 00:26:58,252
He said, "I'm alone."

790
00:26:58,952 --> 00:26:59,982
"Why are you there?"

791
00:27:00,352 --> 00:27:03,222
He got hungry while riding his bike, so he went to the gukbap place.

792
00:27:03,322 --> 00:27:04,461
It was a sundae gukbap place.

793
00:27:04,462 --> 00:27:05,522
Normally...

794
00:27:05,692 --> 00:27:07,461
- It's not easy even for adults...
- No, it's not.

795
00:27:07,462 --> 00:27:09,291
- to eat alone.
- And he's a grade schooler.

796
00:27:09,292 --> 00:27:12,201
Since children grow up really fast...

797
00:27:12,202 --> 00:27:13,461
- these days, - True.

798
00:27:13,462 --> 00:27:16,331
I asked my son to take a photo and show me around.

799
00:27:16,332 --> 00:27:19,042
He was actually at a gukbap restaurant,

800
00:27:19,202 --> 00:27:21,171
eating sundae gukbap by himself.

801
00:27:21,172 --> 00:27:22,572
- That's shocking.
- Unbelievable.

802
00:27:22,672 --> 00:27:25,811
- What he did was quite odd.
- He's interesting.

803
00:27:25,812 --> 00:27:27,352
So I told my wife about it.

804
00:27:27,512 --> 00:27:30,081
"Honey. He's currently eating gukbap alone."

805
00:27:30,082 --> 00:27:32,921
Being in elementary school,

806
00:27:32,922 --> 00:27:34,751
- he's not that sharp yet.
- Right.

807
00:27:34,752 --> 00:27:37,761
The owner of the gukbap restaurant...

808
00:27:37,762 --> 00:27:39,461
- mixed the rice into the soup...
- Oh, my.

809
00:27:39,462 --> 00:27:41,262
and blew on it to cool it down.

810
00:27:42,562 --> 00:27:44,331
- That was a little...
- What an odd child.

811
00:27:44,332 --> 00:27:47,171
- It was like...
- Well, he's a young customer.

812
00:27:47,172 --> 00:27:48,731
- That's weird, Kyung Hwan.
- Right?

813
00:27:48,732 --> 00:27:50,201
Both of you are weird today.

814
00:27:50,202 --> 00:27:52,371
Others might think we don't feed our child at home.

815
00:27:52,372 --> 00:27:53,441
True.

816
00:27:53,442 --> 00:27:54,541
"Did you know about it, honey?"

817
00:27:54,542 --> 00:27:57,141
"He rode his bike to get gukbap by himself."

818
00:27:57,142 --> 00:27:59,341
My wife said, "He even eats sashimi."

819
00:27:59,342 --> 00:28:01,181
- By himself?
- Sashimi by himself.

820
00:28:01,182 --> 00:28:03,011
- Even adults can't do it.
- No.

821
00:28:03,012 --> 00:28:05,152
You need some guts to go to a sashimi place alone.

822
00:28:05,282 --> 00:28:06,921
It must've been a sushi place, right?

823
00:28:06,922 --> 00:28:09,022
No, he ate flatfish sashimi.

824
00:28:10,622 --> 00:28:12,921
- Flatfish sashimi?
- By himself?

825
00:28:12,922 --> 00:28:14,561
- A fifth grader did?
- Yes.

826
00:28:14,562 --> 00:28:16,492
- But flatfish sashimi is delicious.
- I...

827
00:28:16,862 --> 00:28:19,331
I didn't even make it to fifth grade.

828
00:28:19,332 --> 00:28:21,001
When I was in 1st or 2nd grade,

829
00:28:21,002 --> 00:28:23,201
I ate gukbap by myself at the restaurant.

830
00:28:23,202 --> 00:28:25,872
But I'm sure the owner didn't realize you were a child.

831
00:28:26,202 --> 00:28:27,511
I was...

832
00:28:27,512 --> 00:28:30,012
"Sir. The smoking room is over there."

833
00:28:32,012 --> 00:28:34,382
"Sir, smoking is prohibited indoors."

834
00:28:34,752 --> 00:28:37,421
I can't say that was never the case.

835
00:28:37,422 --> 00:28:40,221
Anyway, going there alone isn't...

836
00:28:40,222 --> 00:28:41,391
"He doesn't drink though."

837
00:28:41,392 --> 00:28:43,091
- And what you like is...
- Of course.

838
00:28:43,092 --> 00:28:45,421
- Kids could like it too.
- That's interesting.

839
00:28:45,422 --> 00:28:46,691
Don't assume that kids...

840
00:28:46,692 --> 00:28:47,961
- only love pork cutlets.
- By the way...

841
00:28:47,962 --> 00:28:49,231
- I never had rice soup.
- Right.

842
00:28:49,232 --> 00:28:50,291
- Next.
- It's Kyu Han.

843
00:28:50,292 --> 00:28:52,461
Kyu Han and Hee Jin wrote this...

844
00:28:52,462 --> 00:28:54,871
for their relationship, "My Mister."

845
00:28:54,872 --> 00:28:57,241
This is the play we talked about earlier.

846
00:28:57,242 --> 00:28:59,301
- That's right.
- But isn't this a drama?

847
00:28:59,302 --> 00:29:01,071
- "My Mister" is a drama.
- Yes, it is.

848
00:29:01,072 --> 00:29:03,111
- It's based on that?
- It's a play made from it.

849
00:29:03,112 --> 00:29:05,342
- So they made a play from it.
- That's right.

850
00:29:05,682 --> 00:29:07,111
What are your roles then?

851
00:29:07,112 --> 00:29:08,112
Are you playing Lee Ji An?

852
00:29:08,113 --> 00:29:10,412
Do you think I play Lee Ji An? Of course not.

853
00:29:10,652 --> 00:29:11,821
Are you the mister then?

854
00:29:11,822 --> 00:29:12,822
- What?
- Goodness.

855
00:29:13,282 --> 00:29:14,292
- My goodness.
- Do you play the mister?

856
00:29:14,892 --> 00:29:17,291
- Are you the mister?
- This is the typical Dad Joke.

857
00:29:17,292 --> 00:29:18,992
Then Kyu Han plays the role of IU?

858
00:29:19,362 --> 00:29:21,061
- One of you must be IU.
- So Kyu Han is IU?

859
00:29:21,062 --> 00:29:22,091
Of course.

860
00:29:22,092 --> 00:29:23,731
It must be so fun to watch.

861
00:29:23,732 --> 00:29:25,601
- What do you guys play then?
- No. We play...

862
00:29:25,602 --> 00:29:27,471
I play Yoon Hee in the play.

863
00:29:27,472 --> 00:29:28,472
- Lee Ji Ah's role.
- Lee Ji Ah's role.

864
00:29:28,473 --> 00:29:31,201
- The wife of Park Dong Hoon.
- I see.

865
00:29:31,202 --> 00:29:34,141
I'm the one who has an affair with the wife.

866
00:29:34,142 --> 00:29:35,142
- Gosh.
- You shouldn't.

867
00:29:35,143 --> 00:29:36,571
- It suits you perfectly.
- We have an affair.

868
00:29:36,572 --> 00:29:38,241
So you're the director of the company?

869
00:29:38,242 --> 00:29:39,441
- The CEO.
- You're the CEO.

870
00:29:39,442 --> 00:29:41,681
I play Do Joon Young in the play.

871
00:29:41,682 --> 00:29:44,322
- Who plays the other roles?
- Who's in it?

872
00:29:44,952 --> 00:29:46,422
Park Dong Hoon...

873
00:29:46,682 --> 00:29:48,621
is played by Park Eun Seok and Lee Dong Ha.

874
00:29:48,622 --> 00:29:50,451
- I know them.
- The two play them.

875
00:29:50,452 --> 00:29:51,621
- Lee Ji An is played by...
- I see.

876
00:29:51,622 --> 00:29:53,891
- Hong Ye Ji.
- and Kim Hyun Soo.

877
00:29:53,892 --> 00:29:55,291
- They play that role.
- I heard that...

878
00:29:55,292 --> 00:29:56,731
it was Kyu Han's first play.

879
00:29:56,732 --> 00:29:57,861
Really?

880
00:29:57,862 --> 00:29:58,862
- It's my first time.
- We think he was in it a lot.

881
00:29:58,863 --> 00:30:00,031
Why did we think that?

882
00:30:00,032 --> 00:30:01,501
- We thought you were a veteran.
- I mean...

883
00:30:01,502 --> 00:30:04,641
You seem to be someone who has been in plays a lot.

884
00:30:04,642 --> 00:30:06,871
- Many people think like that.
- Right.

885
00:30:06,872 --> 00:30:09,471
This time, people thought...

886
00:30:09,472 --> 00:30:11,011
- I had a lot of experience.
- Right.

887
00:30:11,012 --> 00:30:12,381
So when I told them it was my first time,

888
00:30:12,382 --> 00:30:13,511
they were all surprised.

889
00:30:13,512 --> 00:30:15,752
But actually, I made my debut in a drama.

890
00:30:16,082 --> 00:30:18,281
- But your vocalization suits plays.
- I see.

891
00:30:18,282 --> 00:30:20,181
- Right.
- "Hey, you."

892
00:30:20,182 --> 00:30:21,251
This is how you do it.

893
00:30:21,252 --> 00:30:22,722
- What?
- What's that?

894
00:30:23,092 --> 00:30:25,021
- Kyu Han.
- "Hey, you."

895
00:30:25,022 --> 00:30:26,621
- "Hey, you."
- I mean...

896
00:30:26,622 --> 00:30:28,431
- Yes. He does abdominal breathing.
- Right.

897
00:30:28,432 --> 00:30:30,231
- That's what he does.
- It's because of that.

898
00:30:30,232 --> 00:30:31,901
I do that a little,

899
00:30:31,902 --> 00:30:33,631
but since I practice a lot these days,

900
00:30:33,632 --> 00:30:35,902
my voice became more powerful.

901
00:30:36,402 --> 00:30:37,871
Were you interested in plays?

902
00:30:37,872 --> 00:30:39,171
- I really wanted to do it.
- You did?

903
00:30:39,172 --> 00:30:40,642
I wanted to do it so much,

904
00:30:40,812 --> 00:30:42,471
but because I had no experience at all,

905
00:30:42,472 --> 00:30:44,211
- I was afraid to try it.
- Of course.

906
00:30:44,212 --> 00:30:45,841
And I was worried about trying it...

907
00:30:45,842 --> 00:30:47,412
and getting criticized.

908
00:30:47,752 --> 00:30:50,511
- Those thoughts made me hesitant.
- Of course.

909
00:30:50,512 --> 00:30:54,221
But I thought it was now or never,

910
00:30:54,222 --> 00:30:55,321
- so I decided to try it.
- I see.

911
00:30:55,322 --> 00:30:56,551
- It will start next week.
- Did it...

912
00:30:56,552 --> 00:30:57,761
- On the 22nd.
- Did it start? Or...

913
00:30:57,762 --> 00:30:59,561
- When does it begin?
- It starts on August 22.

914
00:30:59,562 --> 00:31:01,061
This episode will be aired on August 23.

915
00:31:01,062 --> 00:31:02,231
so I'd say it started yesterday.

916
00:31:02,232 --> 00:31:04,101
- I see.
- You take care of him a lot.

917
00:31:04,102 --> 00:31:06,432
- The two are...
- It's because Hee Jin is in it.

918
00:31:08,449 --> 00:31:10,718
(A sudden flirting)

919
00:31:10,719 --> 00:31:12,579
Gosh, what's that?

920
00:31:13,049 --> 00:31:14,788
My goodness.

921
00:31:14,789 --> 00:31:15,789
Hold on.

922
00:31:16,319 --> 00:31:17,488
He's the one who likes it the most.

923
00:31:17,489 --> 00:31:19,459
Whenever I say something like this...

924
00:31:20,059 --> 00:31:23,628
- Why do you love it so much?
- Hee Jin might get confused.

925
00:31:23,629 --> 00:31:25,458
Why are you so excited?

926
00:31:25,459 --> 00:31:28,028
Seriously. Jang Hoon is her mister here.

927
00:31:28,029 --> 00:31:29,068
- Thank you, Jang Hoon.
- Hold on. While Jang Hoon...

928
00:31:29,069 --> 00:31:30,069
and all of us are laughing,

929
00:31:30,070 --> 00:31:31,899
Yeong Cheol doesn't look happy about it.

930
00:31:32,039 --> 00:31:33,039
(Embarrassed)

931
00:31:33,040 --> 00:31:34,238
- I'm not.
- He is...

932
00:31:34,239 --> 00:31:36,668
I sorry, but are you comparing Yeong Cheol...

933
00:31:36,669 --> 00:31:37,708
- and me?
- Because we put you together...

934
00:31:37,709 --> 00:31:40,808
- Did it make you upset?
- You put us together in this.

935
00:31:40,809 --> 00:31:42,108
No, we didn't.

936
00:31:42,109 --> 00:31:43,448
It's just that Yeong Cheol keeps getting in between you two.

937
00:31:43,449 --> 00:31:45,518
- I see.
- Don't worry about it.

938
00:31:45,519 --> 00:31:46,648
By the way,

939
00:31:46,649 --> 00:31:48,348
- I was in a play too.
- It wasn't like that.

940
00:31:48,349 --> 00:31:49,788
You need to memorize all the lines.

941
00:31:49,789 --> 00:31:51,318
- Right.
- There are no prompters.

942
00:31:51,319 --> 00:31:52,888
- No.
- Of course not.

943
00:31:52,889 --> 00:31:55,059
How do you memorize all those lines?

944
00:31:55,289 --> 00:31:57,528
Well for me, even when I'm in a drama...

945
00:31:57,529 --> 00:31:58,598
I'm a bit impatient,

946
00:31:58,599 --> 00:32:00,128
so I have to memorize them all.

947
00:32:00,129 --> 00:32:01,168
- Goodness.
- Gosh.

948
00:32:01,169 --> 00:32:04,398
I have to memorize them all to do my daily routines.

949
00:32:04,399 --> 00:32:06,098
- He has his own system.
- When I'm in a drama,

950
00:32:06,099 --> 00:32:07,768
it's okay to memorize each scene. Just the ones I'll be shooting...

951
00:32:07,769 --> 00:32:08,769
- that day and move on.
- Right.

952
00:32:08,770 --> 00:32:10,278
- That's right.
- But I must memorize everything.

953
00:32:10,279 --> 00:32:11,338
- Yes.
- Because it's a play.

954
00:32:11,339 --> 00:32:13,509
- Right.
- So it was too much for me too.

955
00:32:13,879 --> 00:32:15,648
By the way, Kyu Han, I have a question about plays.

956
00:32:15,649 --> 00:32:18,418
Do you have to make everything the same as the script?

957
00:32:18,419 --> 00:32:20,588
Or do you act according to the situation?

958
00:32:20,589 --> 00:32:21,948
Well, that's not the case.

959
00:32:21,949 --> 00:32:24,588
Because there are so many unexpected variables during the play...

960
00:32:24,589 --> 00:32:26,788
I don't know that well since it's my first time,

961
00:32:26,789 --> 00:32:28,358
but considering what the actors and the staff members told me,

962
00:32:28,359 --> 00:32:30,728
when someone makes a mistake,

963
00:32:30,729 --> 00:32:32,728
the partner covers up for them.

964
00:32:32,729 --> 00:32:34,298
- I see.
- That's how it goes.

965
00:32:34,299 --> 00:32:36,029
- So...
- Then Hee Jin memorized them all?

966
00:32:36,569 --> 00:32:38,269
- She can't even memorize the names.
- Of course.

967
00:32:38,699 --> 00:32:39,699
(Feeling guilty)

968
00:32:39,700 --> 00:32:41,508
- That's true.
- Right.

969
00:32:41,509 --> 00:32:43,308
- She couldn't memorize the names.
- Kyu Han told us already.

970
00:32:43,309 --> 00:32:44,808
How can she memorize the whole thing when she can't memorize the names?

971
00:32:44,809 --> 00:32:46,908
But it's a relief.

972
00:32:46,909 --> 00:32:48,448
During the 20 years of acting,

973
00:32:48,449 --> 00:32:51,049
