974
00:32:51,779 --> 00:32:53,378
But for a play...

975
00:32:53,379 --> 00:32:55,388
Like he said, it's different.

976
00:32:55,389 --> 00:32:57,088
We're used to shooting a scene...

977
00:32:57,089 --> 00:32:58,818
and forgetting the lines for the scene when we're done.

978
00:32:58,819 --> 00:33:00,988
- That's like a habit for us.
- Right. In a drama.

979
00:33:00,989 --> 00:33:02,758
So even when I memorized them,

980
00:33:02,759 --> 00:33:04,998
I forget them the next day.

981
00:33:04,999 --> 00:33:06,968
I have to memorize them again, but I forget them again.

982
00:33:06,969 --> 00:33:08,928
This keeps on repeating.

983
00:33:08,929 --> 00:33:10,568
- So...
- Like the movie "Memento?"

984
00:33:10,569 --> 00:33:12,568
- I couldn't memorize them all.
- Write them on your body.

985
00:33:12,569 --> 00:33:15,368
- You need to write them on you.
- Why would you forget them all?

986
00:33:15,369 --> 00:33:16,808
- I don't know.
- So she couldn't memorize it.

987
00:33:16,809 --> 00:33:18,139
- That's what she means.
- Oh, right.

988
00:33:18,609 --> 00:33:19,838
So you memorize them just for the day.

989
00:33:19,839 --> 00:33:22,748
She told me, "Gosh. I can't memorize the lines."

990
00:33:22,749 --> 00:33:23,749
"How did you memorize them?"

991
00:33:23,750 --> 00:33:25,578
