- I see.

1079
00:36:12,749 --> 00:36:14,018
- With me?
- Yes.

1080
00:36:14,019 --> 00:36:16,688
You might think that video was about me...

1081
00:36:16,689 --> 00:36:18,858
- me doing a blind date, but...
- That's not true.

1082
00:36:18,859 --> 00:36:20,788
She...

1083
00:36:20,789 --> 00:36:22,828
- Hee Jin looks upset.
- No, I'm not.

1084
00:36:22,829 --> 00:36:24,828
- Seriously.
- Hee Jin, he says that's not it.

1085
00:36:24,829 --> 00:36:26,958
- My goodness.
- It's a misunderstanding.

1086
00:36:26,959 --> 00:36:30,368
She's someone who hosts shows...

1087
00:36:30,369 --> 00:36:32,068
with Jun Gyu.

1088
00:36:32,069 --> 00:36:33,769
Gosh, Hee Jin. What a relief.

1089
00:36:34,939 --> 00:36:36,808
- Because the blind date...
- It wasn't a blind date.

1090
00:36:36,809 --> 00:36:39,908
Jun Gyu was joking, saying that it was a blind date.

1091
00:36:39,909 --> 00:36:41,408
- That's what it is.
- Right.

1092
00:36:41,409 --> 00:36:44,748
By the way, you have a Guinness record, right?

1093
00:36:44,749 --> 00:36:45,749
- Oh, right.
- What is it?

1094
00:36:45,750 --> 00:36:48,488
I have my Guinness record at home.

1095
00:36:48,489 --> 00:36:51,458
It has the Guinness record symbol, written in English.

1096
00:36:51,459 --> 00:36:53,858
My name, Park Jun Gyu, is written on it.

1097
00:36:53,859 --> 00:36:55,228
So I have a Guinness record.

1098
00:36:55,229 --> 00:36:57,399
It's playing golf for 75 holes a day.

1099
00:36:58,229 --> 00:36:59,358
- A day?
- You played 75 holes?

1100
00:36:59,359 --> 00:37:00,928
That's impossible.

1101
00:37:00,929 --> 00:37:04,698
- I played 75 holes a day.
- Really?

1102
00:37:04,699 --> 00:37:08,139
(He started at 4:40am.)

1103
00:37:08,739 --> 00:37:13,279
(Guinness Park played golf for 16 hours.)

1104
00:37:13,479 --> 00:37:15,578
Goodness. Playing 75 holes is amazing.

1105
00:37:15,579 --> 00:37:16,778
I had to hurry and play all the holes.

1106
00:37:16,779 --> 00:37:19,348
Next for remarks. Kyu Han wrote...

1107
00:37:19,349 --> 00:37:20,988
Mr. Meticulous.

1108
00:37:20,989 --> 00:37:22,648
- Mr. Meticulous?
- Meticulous.

1109
00:37:22,649 --> 00:37:24,818
- I plan things...
- Right.

1110
00:37:24,819 --> 00:37:25,988
- in details.
- He's a planner.

1111
00:37:25,989 --> 00:37:27,188
- I'm a planner.
- He's meticulous.

1112
00:37:27,189 --> 00:37:29,188
I get up every day...

1113
00:37:29,189 --> 00:37:31,228
to the daily routines.

1114
00:37:31,229 --> 00:37:32,229
- Really?
- All those.

1115
00:37:32,230 --> 00:37:33,498
He doesn't get old.

1116
00:37:33,499 --> 00:37:35,569
I want things to be settled.

1117
00:37:35,899 --> 00:37:37,468
I'm a bit obsessed with it.

1118
00:37:37,469 --> 00:37:38,568
His body is fit too.

1119
00:37:38,569 --> 00:37:39,998
You were never late to work?

1120
00:37:39,999 --> 00:37:41,708
- Late to work?
- I don't think he has.

1121
00:37:41,709 --> 00:37:42,768
If there was a natural disaster,

1122
00:37:42,769 --> 00:37:44,008
- A natural disaster?
- or...

1123
00:37:44,009 --> 00:37:45,608
- Except for that.
- You'll be late when it happens.

1124
00:37:45,609 --> 00:37:47,508
- That's understandable.
- Or if my manager or coworkers...

1125
00:37:47,509 --> 00:37:49,748
- were late, I was late too.
- Right.

1126
00:37:49,749 --> 00:37:51,548
- When others were late.
- Except for that,

1127
00:37:51,549 --> 00:37:53,648
- I was never late because of me.
- But...

1128
00:37:53,649 --> 00:37:54,948
Then how do you go on a trip abroad?

1129
00:37:54,949 --> 00:37:56,048
Let's say you go abroad.

1130
00:37:56,049 --> 00:37:58,118
Usually, when I go abroad,

1131
00:37:58,119 --> 00:38:00,518
I set a schedule from leaving to arrival.

1132
00:38:00,519 --> 00:38:01,858
- I plan everything.
- You plan everything.

1133
00:38:01,859 --> 00:38:03,728
You don't let it fall? You must do it as is?

1134
00:38:03,729 --> 00:38:04,858
I should stick to the plan.

1135
00:38:04,859 --> 00:38:06,498
- Gosh, that's amazing.
- Isn't it tiring?

1136
00:38:06,499 --> 00:38:07,928
I like being tired because of it.

1137
00:38:07,929 --> 00:38:08,929
- I like that.
- Is that so?

1138
00:38:08,930 --> 00:38:09,968
Since I'm on a trip...

1139
00:38:09,969 --> 00:38:11,469
It's just that he was never in a really tough situation.

1140
00:38:12,469 --> 00:38:13,498
That's right.

1141
00:38:13,499 --> 00:38:16,008
People who have never struggled...

1142
00:38:16,009 --> 00:38:17,309
say such things.

1143
00:38:17,439 --> 00:38:18,908
"I want to be exhausted."

1144
00:38:18,909 --> 00:38:21,508
"I want to suffer." It's because he's never experienced that.

1145
00:38:21,509 --> 00:38:22,608
You're really an old man.

1146
00:38:22,609 --> 00:38:23,709
I'm sorry.

1147
00:38:24,279 --> 00:38:25,778
You're totally an old man.

1148
00:38:25,779 --> 00:38:26,948
Hold on.

1149
00:38:26,949 --> 00:38:28,988
When you go abroad,

1150
00:38:28,989 --> 00:38:31,259
- you may get jet lag, - Exactly.

1151
00:38:31,559 --> 00:38:34,328
- and the situation may change.
- When you go alone...

1152
00:38:34,329 --> 00:38:36,528
In my case, I prepare backup plans...

1153
00:38:36,529 --> 00:38:38,359
to adapt to the situations.

1154
00:38:39,199 --> 00:38:40,199
- Really?
- A...

1155
00:38:40,399 --> 00:38:42,098
Say we decided to go to a certain restaurant,

1156
00:38:42,099 --> 00:38:44,198
but there are no seats left when we go there.

1157
00:38:44,199 --> 00:38:45,469
Then we go to the next location.

1158
00:38:45,539 --> 00:38:46,869
I don't think about things there.

1159
00:38:47,099 --> 00:38:48,338
"This restaurant is full? Okay."

1160
00:38:48,339 --> 00:38:49,868
- What if there's a traffic jam?
- Traffic jam?

1161
00:38:49,869 --> 00:38:51,038
- He walks.
- I calculate the time...

1162
00:38:51,039 --> 00:38:52,209
we'll spend stuck in the traffic jam.

1163
00:38:52,739 --> 00:38:54,208
- Hee Jin wouldn't be able...
- I remember.

1164
00:38:54,209 --> 00:38:56,508
to go on a trip with someone like Kyu Han.

1165
00:38:56,509 --> 00:38:59,178
After the play,

1166
00:38:59,179 --> 00:39:02,348
Kyu Han said he'd take everyone...

1167
00:39:02,349 --> 00:39:04,518
- on a trip...
- That's so nice.

1168
00:39:04,519 --> 00:39:06,358
- to Vietnam.
- So nice.

1169
00:39:06,359 --> 00:39:09,189
- It will be a tough trip.
- I've never heard this before.

1170
00:39:09,929 --> 00:39:11,858
- You're planning to drop out?
- A tough trip.

1171
00:39:11,859 --> 00:39:13,299
I'm thinking about it now.

1172
00:39:13,459 --> 00:39:15,098
I'm also a planner, but I'm not this hardcore.

1173
00:39:15,099 --> 00:39:16,768
- Don't go.
- But it's going to be convenient.

1174
00:39:16,769 --> 00:39:18,298
- I travelled recently...
- Vietnam...

1175
00:39:18,299 --> 00:39:19,838
with my manager.

1176
00:39:19,839 --> 00:39:21,008
I had a reality check.

1177
00:39:21,009 --> 00:39:22,409
My manager suddenly said,

1178
00:39:22,709 --> 00:39:25,078
- "Can I just rest today?
- Right.

1179
00:39:25,079 --> 00:39:26,378
- I guess it was uncomfortable.
- I said,

1180
00:39:26,379 --> 00:39:28,748
"We came here to rest."

1181
00:39:28,749 --> 00:39:31,248
"Why are you saying you want to rest?"

1182
00:39:31,249 --> 00:39:33,019
(Goodness)

1183
00:39:33,849 --> 00:39:35,818
- He's the worst.
- Old man!

1184
00:39:35,819 --> 00:39:37,589
- I'm worried about this.
- Old man!

1185
00:39:37,759 --> 00:39:41,228
Last time you came you talked about waxing.

1186
00:39:41,229 --> 00:39:42,458
Do you still do it?

1187
00:39:42,459 --> 00:39:44,398
I always do.

1188
00:39:44,399 --> 00:39:45,998
It's not permanent hair removal?

1189
00:39:45,999 --> 00:39:47,298
It's not permanent.

1190
00:39:47,299 --> 00:39:48,799
These days,

1191
00:39:49,129 --> 00:39:52,038
I don't need someone to do it for me. I do it myself.

1192
00:39:52,039 --> 00:39:53,068
Right.

1193
00:39:53,069 --> 00:39:55,508
