00:48:05,399 --> 00:48:08,269
What does "SOBP" mean? I heard that's your nickname.

1440
00:48:08,499 --> 00:48:11,299
There was a time when I was so busy,

1441
00:48:11,439 --> 00:48:13,399
so I had the schedule of BLACKPINK.

1442
00:48:14,399 --> 00:48:16,569
- "SOBP?"
- I was incredibly busy.

1443
00:48:16,869 --> 00:48:18,908
I couldn't even go home.

1444
00:48:18,909 --> 00:48:21,709
Old guys always make such fun nicknames.

1445
00:48:21,879 --> 00:48:23,478
I thought it was something like Heartsping.

1446
00:48:23,479 --> 00:48:24,948
I couldn't even go home.

1447
00:48:24,949 --> 00:48:26,878
BLACKPINK performs...

1448
00:48:26,879 --> 00:48:28,818
- in Paris...
- That's right.

1449
00:48:28,819 --> 00:48:30,989
and other places abroad,

1450
00:48:31,189 --> 00:48:33,758
and they must stay in hotels, right?

1451
00:48:33,759 --> 00:48:35,528
I stayed in motels.

1452
00:48:35,529 --> 00:48:38,058
They have motels in front of the studio.

1453
00:48:38,059 --> 00:48:39,128
- Really? Why?
- Yes.

1454
00:48:39,129 --> 00:48:40,298
But motels are nice these days.

1455
00:48:40,299 --> 00:48:41,629
So you go to work straight from there?

1456
00:48:41,829 --> 00:48:43,768
- Since you have several shows?
- If I have the first and last show,

1457
00:48:43,769 --> 00:48:45,838
the last show finishes at 2am.

1458
00:48:45,839 --> 00:48:46,868
In the morning?

1459
00:48:46,869 --> 00:48:48,438
And if I have the first show,

1460
00:48:48,439 --> 00:48:50,039
it starts at 5 or 6am.

1461
00:48:50,369 --> 00:48:52,179
Then I don't have time to go home.

1462
00:48:52,339 --> 00:48:55,779
That's why I have to go to a motel or hotel nearby,

1463
00:48:55,879 --> 00:48:58,819
sleep, and come right back out for the live broadcast.

1464
00:48:59,019 --> 00:49:01,518
If you had to sleep at motels and had the SOBP,

1465
00:49:01,519 --> 00:49:03,689
then you must have earned a lot of money.

1466
00:49:03,749 --> 00:49:05,889
What a lot of people misunderstand is that...

1467
00:49:06,219 --> 00:49:08,188
even if the items sell out...

1468
00:49:08,189 --> 00:49:09,858
and I sell more than a million dollars' worth,

1469
00:49:09,859 --> 00:49:10,989
it's not my money.

1470
00:49:11,599 --> 00:49:15,968
It's the money the CEO of that item's company earned,

1471
00:49:15,969 --> 00:49:18,998
and I only get the fixed appearance payment.

1472
00:49:18,999 --> 00:49:20,599
You don't have an incentive?

1473
00:49:20,639 --> 00:49:21,909
That depends on the contract.

1474
00:49:22,169 --> 00:49:23,968
For me, I don't take incentives.

1475
00:49:23,969 --> 00:49:25,878
But even the appearance payment must be a lot,

1476
00:49:25,879 --> 00:49:27,538
- since you have so many shows.
- I know.

1477
00:49:27,539 --> 00:49:28,548
He does have a lot.

1478
00:49:28,549 --> 00:49:30,809
Then you must have earned quite a lot until now.

1479
00:49:31,209 --> 00:49:32,619
Not as much as you.

1480
00:49:33,779 --> 00:49:34,848
- Even if I got a lot, - That's right.

1481
00:49:34,849 --> 00:49:36,389
- it won't be as much.
- He has a lot.

1482
00:49:36,949 --> 00:49:38,119
He's untouchable.

1483
00:49:38,289 --> 00:49:39,659
I didn't make this up.

1484
00:49:39,719 --> 00:49:42,228
- Actually, Sang Min once tried it.
- Home shopping.

1485
00:49:42,229 --> 00:49:44,029
- Yes, home shopping.
- So I asked him...

1486
00:49:44,059 --> 00:49:45,728
how it went.

1487
00:49:45,729 --> 00:49:48,728
He said you needed to study far more than you'd think.

1488
00:49:48,729 --> 00:49:50,028
- Yes, that's right.
- He said it was so hard.

1489
00:49:50,029 --> 00:49:51,338
- He's still doing it.
- You need to study hard.

1490
00:49:51,339 --> 00:49:52,638
Now, I only do my products.

1491
00:49:52,639 --> 00:49:54,638
It's not only about being eloquent, is it?

1492
00:49:54,639 --> 00:49:57,238
Sure. I need to use it myself, study it,

1493
00:49:57,239 --> 00:49:59,078
try it, and research about it,

1494
00:49:59,079 --> 00:50:01,708
or no one else would listen to me trying to sell it.

1495
00:50:01,709 --> 00:50:03,909
- That's amazing.
- So now,

1496
00:50:03,979 --> 00:50:06,949
I need to look at the product description,

1497
00:50:07,179 --> 00:50:10,188
memorize it, and talk about what I experienced and felt.

1498
00:50:10,189 --> 00:50:12,789
You have been doing live shows for 20 years now.

1499
00:50:13,459 --> 00:50:15,758
He must have overcome all the unexpected issues.

1500
00:50:15,759 --> 00:50:17,628
When we have theater shows,

1501
00:50:17,629 --> 00:50:20,158
we need to memorize our lines...

1502
00:50:20,159 --> 00:50:22,528
until we can recite them at any moment.

1503
00:50:22,529 --> 00:50:24,738
Then do you also memorize everything...

1504
00:50:24,739 --> 00:50:26,899
for the live shows?

1505
00:50:27,139 --> 00:50:28,868
Well, for the live shows,

1506
00:50:28,869 --> 00:50:30,438
if it's olive oil, for example,

1507
00:50:30,439 --> 00:50:32,708
and people came in after watching Men on a Mission,

1508
00:50:32,709 --> 00:50:34,479
- we need to grab their attention.
- Yes, olive oil.

1509
00:50:34,539 --> 00:50:36,378
This is from the young olives...

1510
00:50:36,379 --> 00:50:39,078
that grow into grape-sized ones starting in July and August.

1511
00:50:39,079 --> 00:50:41,318
These have the highest content of polyphenol.

1512
00:50:41,319 --> 00:50:44,388
They hand-pick these manually.

1513
00:50:44,389 --> 00:50:46,418
It's not meant for mass production by using machines.

1514
00:50:46,419 --> 00:50:48,359
In order to consume in the morning on an empty stomach,

1515
00:50:48,389 --> 00:50:49,888
the acidity needs to be low.

1516
00:50:49,889 --> 00:50:52,858
Extra premium virgin oil needs to be lower than 0.8,

1517
00:50:52,859 --> 00:50:54,258
in order to get the highest grade.

1518
00:50:54,259 --> 00:50:57,198
This goes as low as 0.17,

1519
00:50:57,199 --> 00:50:59,368
so when you consume it in the morning on an empty stomach,

1520
00:50:59,369 --> 00:51:01,608
it has to be from Spain, made with Picual single-variety,

1521
00:51:01,609 --> 00:51:04,538
grown organic in the Andalusia Jaen region.

1522
00:51:04,539 --> 00:51:07,238
That's what you need to have a comfortable stomach.

1523
00:51:07,239 --> 00:51:08,308
- That's how I do it.
- Gosh.

1524
00:51:08,309 --> 00:51:11,678
You should also try the lemon juice.

1525
00:51:11,679 --> 00:51:12,718
- Lemon juice?
- Lemon juice?

1526
00:51:12,719 --> 00:51:15,489
We're heading to Spain, the top producer of lemons.

1527
00:51:15,549 --> 00:51:17,348
Usually, we squeeze lemons,

1528
00:51:17,349 --> 00:51:20,058
and it's called the squeeze, but the skin is thrown away.

1529
00:51:20,059 --> 00:51:22,958
No way. The skin has all the good nutrients,

1530
00:51:22,959 --> 00:51:25,898
which is why we need to eat...

1531
00:51:25,899 --> 00:51:27,158
the white part of the grapefruit as well.

1532
00:51:27,159 --> 00:51:30,328
This has the skin, pulp, seeds, all in one packet.

1533
00:51:30,329 --> 00:51:31,539
This is what you need to eat.

1534
00:51:31,669 --> 00:51:32,799
Like so.

1535
00:51:33,199 --> 00:51:34,498
- That's amazing.
- Then,

1536
00:51:34,499 --> 00:51:35,938
what is the most preferred item...

1537
00:51:35,939 --> 00:51:37,739
by show hosts?

1538
00:51:38,479 --> 00:51:40,808
We do have the items that are easier,

1539
00:51:40,809 --> 00:51:42,678
and those that we don't prefer.

1540
00:51:42,679 --> 00:51:44,919
For food, it's lobster.

1541
00:51:45,649 --> 00:51:47,548
- Gosh.
- Do you eat all of it?

1542
00:51:47,549 --> 00:51:48,718
We do eat it all.

1543
00:51:48,719 --> 00:51:50,488
- It's tasty.
- Lobster, snow crab,

1544
00:51:50,489 --> 00:51:51,888
and raw tuna.

1545
00:51:51,889 --> 00:51:53,918
- Expensive and tasty things?
- These things.

1546
00:51:53,919 --> 00:51:56,329
- It doesn't come often.
- Because it's easy to swallow.

1547
00:51:56,459 --> 00:51:58,498
It's easy to swallow quickly after chewing,

1548
00:51:58,499 --> 00:52:00,059
- since we have to talk.
- That's right.

1549
00:52:00,299 --> 00:52:02,668
Then what's difficult?

1550
00:52:02,669 --> 00:52:04,028
Difficult things...

1551
00:52:04,029 --> 00:52:05,369
for food would be...

1552
00:52:05,639 --> 00:52:07,368
- sweet potato.
- It's dry.

1553
00:52:07,369 --> 00:52:09,708
Not only is it dry, but it's hot.

1554
00:52:09,709 --> 00:52:10,938
Like this?

1555
00:52:10,939 --> 00:52:12,309
The roof of your mouth.

1556
00:52:12,339 --> 00:52:14,608
- If you open the sweet potato, - It has to steam.

1557
00:52:14,609 --> 00:52:16,448
- The steam.
- the steam comes up,

1558
00:52:16,449 --> 00:52:18,348
- and it has to be shown on camera.
- It has to be piping hot.

1559
00:52:18,349 --> 00:52:19,878
Beginners will immediately put that...

1560
00:52:19,879 --> 00:52:21,378
in their mouth.

1561
00:52:21,379 --> 00:52:22,718
- That's hot.
- They will burn their mouth.

1562
00:52:22,719 --> 00:52:24,959
We place kimchi on top.

1563
00:52:25,319 --> 00:52:26,518
(Beginners don't know this secret.)

1564
00:52:26,519 --> 00:52:28,328
- You go like this.
- That's crazy.

1565
00:52:28,329 --> 00:52:30,488
You place the kimchi on your tongue,

1566
00:52:30,489 --> 00:52:32,329
- and if you chew like that, - Gosh.

1567
00:52:32,659 --> 00:52:34,499
the cold from the kimchi will mix it up.

1568
00:52:35,099 --> 00:52:36,699
If they don't have kimchi,

1569
00:52:37,129 --> 00:52:38,999
you need to grab the dongchimi, and say,

1570
00:52:39,369 --> 00:52:41,568
"With sweet potato, you need dongchimi."

1571
00:52:41,569 --> 00:52:44,438
Then you first take a sip of it,

1572
00:52:44,439 --> 00:52:45,938
- then add the sweet potato.
- That's it.

1573
00:52:45,939 --> 00:52:48,348
Then it gets neutralized.

1574
00:52:48,349 --> 00:52:50,508
And things like salted oysters are really difficult.

1575
00:52:50,509 --> 00:52:51,778
- Why?
- Nothing can help with that.

1576
00:52:51,779 --> 00:52:52,918
It's salty.

1577
00:52:52,919 --> 00:52:54,648
For salted oysters,

1578
00:52:54,649 --> 00:52:56,018
shows are usually held in the winter.

1579
00:52:56,019 --> 00:52:57,619
So, it's almost in season.

1580
00:52:57,719 --> 00:53:00,218
Usually, when we eat, we take just one oyster...

1581
00:53:00,219 --> 00:53:02,689
- on top of our spoonful of rice.
- Sure.

1582
00:53:02,889 --> 00:53:05,258
- On camera, one oyster won't show.
- It won't do.

1583
00:53:05,259 --> 00:53:06,599
It doesn't look appealing.

1584
00:53:06,999 --> 00:53:08,169
You need to scoop a lot.

1585
00:53:08,629 --> 00:53:09,799
Like this.

1586
00:53:10,929 --> 00:53:12,199
- You need to eat the whole lot.
- Gosh.

1587
00:53:12,399 --> 00:53:14,468
Then the oysters...

1588
00:53:14,469 --> 00:53:16,669
are all salted, right?

1589
00:53:17,369 --> 00:53:19,739
You need to eat that for 60 minutes straight.

1590
00:53:19,879 --> 00:53:21,549
After the show,

1591
00:53:22,409 --> 00:53:24,978
you can't help but drink...

1592
00:53:24,979 --> 00:53:26,948
at least the whole two-liter bottle of water.

1593
00:53:26,949 --> 00:53:29,148
In order to balance out the saltiness.

1594
00:53:29,149 --> 00:53:31,518
That's why some food can be hard.

1595
00:53:31,519 --> 00:53:34,288
I watch a lot of home shopping shows,

1596
00:53:34,289 --> 00:53:37,758
and once I saw him working so hard,

1597
00:53:37,759 --> 00:53:38,958
so I bought it.

1598
00:53:38,959 --> 00:53:40,199
- What was it?
- It was...

1599
00:53:40,499 --> 00:53:42,968
- I really love oranges.
- Yes, oranges.

1600
00:53:42,969 --> 00:53:45,239
I really love oranges.

1601
00:53:45,369 --> 00:53:50,108
It was about a whole truck of oranges.

1602
00:53:50,109 --> 00:53:51,169
Did you see that one?

1603
00:53:52,109 --> 00:53:54,109
- Kyung Hwan was sitting in it.
- Really?

1604
00:53:54,409 --> 00:53:56,408
He just had his face out,

1605
00:53:56,409 --> 00:53:58,219
and the rest was all oranges.

1606
00:53:58,479 --> 00:53:59,948
We made a pool of oranges.

1607
00:53:59,949 --> 00:54:02,349
It looks really fun, right?

1608
00:54:02,689 --> 00:54:05,488
I nearly got frostbite all over my body.

1609
00:54:05,489 --> 00:54:06,889
- Really?
- Because...

1610
00:54:07,019 --> 00:54:08,588
