1612
00:54:10,689 --> 00:54:13,459
The oranges were like hail.

1613
00:54:13,799 --> 00:54:15,628
I had to submerge my body under the oranges...

1614
00:54:15,629 --> 00:54:17,669
and leave just my head out.

1615
00:54:18,469 --> 00:54:21,968
"Oranges from the US."

1616
00:54:21,969 --> 00:54:24,568
And the frozen oranges were so cold.

1617
00:54:24,569 --> 00:54:26,278
But we had to make it fun.

1618
00:54:26,279 --> 00:54:29,679
I know. I could tell...

1619
00:54:29,879 --> 00:54:31,818
- That's amazing.
- how hard he was working.

1620
00:54:31,819 --> 00:54:35,488
Since I do like oranges,

1621
00:54:35,489 --> 00:54:36,918
I did place an order.

1622
00:54:36,919 --> 00:54:38,589
He's our customer, then.

1623
00:54:38,789 --> 00:54:40,618
This won't be easy, but...

1624
00:54:40,619 --> 00:54:41,759
If we were products.

1625
00:54:42,259 --> 00:54:43,728
We do have a lot of flaws, but...

1626
00:54:43,729 --> 00:54:45,898
The products? Gosh, that's not easy.

1627
00:54:45,899 --> 00:54:46,899
You need to sell us.

1628
00:54:46,900 --> 00:54:48,158
- How much?
- That's not easy.

1629
00:54:48,159 --> 00:54:49,899
It's hard to sell people,

1630
00:54:50,099 --> 00:54:53,369
so I will imagine that you are farm and fishery products.

1631
00:54:54,239 --> 00:54:56,408
I'll try and sell just a few products.

1632
00:54:56,409 --> 00:54:57,439
- That's it.
- Okay.

1633
00:54:57,609 --> 00:54:59,078
- He's really amazing.
- He will sell us.

1634
00:54:59,079 --> 00:55:00,839
So many choices.

1635
00:55:01,379 --> 00:55:03,079
- For example...
- That's nice.

1636
00:55:03,379 --> 00:55:05,418
Kyung Hwan, Men on a Mission ends soon.

1637
00:55:05,419 --> 00:55:06,448
- We'll be on live next.
- Okay.

1638
00:55:06,449 --> 00:55:07,649
It's over. On cue!

1639
00:55:07,719 --> 00:55:10,488
Hello, everyone. You just watched a fun show, right?

